      "value": {
        "latex": "\\'Etudier la finitude des sommes suivantes~:",
        "html": "<p>Étudier la finitude des sommes suivantes :</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "2bc9e8ef-dd0f-4bee-8302-c17a98544644",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$\\sum_{(i,j)\\in(\\N^*)^2}\\frac1{(i+j)^\\alpha}$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\sum_{(i,j)\\in(\\N^*)^2}\\frac1{(i+j)^\\alpha}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "c5d77be9-872e-471d-9d55-4b05a6ce62b7",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Regroupement à $i+j$ constant $ \\Rightarrow $ CV ssi $\\alpha > 2$.",
        "html": "<p>Regroupement à <span class=\"math inline\">\\(i+j\\)</span> constant <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Rightarrow\\)</span> CV ssi <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\alpha &gt; 2\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "39d9d593-6079-4c25-9e44-09df86c424d6",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$\\sum_{(i,j)\\in(\\N^*)^2}\\frac1{\\strut i^\\alpha +j^\\alpha}$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\sum_{(i,j)\\in(\\N^*)^2}\\frac1{\\strut i^\\alpha +j^\\alpha}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "f5724bc5-aa0e-49e6-8500-fcd3f094cb02",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Pour $\\alpha\\ge 1$ on a par convexité~:\n             $2^{1-\\alpha}(i+j)^\\alpha \\le i^\\alpha+j^\\alpha \\le (i+j)^\\alpha$\n             donc il y a convergence ssi $\\alpha > 2$.",
        "html": "<p>Pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\alpha\\ge 1\\)</span> on a par convexité : <span class=\"math inline\">\\(2^{1-\\alpha}(i+j)^\\alpha \\le i^\\alpha+j^\\alpha \\le (i+j)^\\alpha\\)</span> donc il y a convergence ssi <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\alpha &gt; 2\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "f202e490-d7fb-408d-8b57-bd55eed10212",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$\\sum_{x\\in\\Q\\cap[1,+\\infty[}\\frac1{x^2}$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\sum_{x\\in\\Q\\cap[1,+\\infty[}\\frac1{x^2}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "8c1f458c-c36f-4dc8-8bcf-6c5e9dbf0aa5",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Il y a une infinité de termes supérieurs à~$1/4$.",
        "html": "<p>Il y a une infinité de termes supérieurs à <span class=\"math inline\">\\(1/4\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
